===Bibliography=== {{refbegin|2}} * {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Donskis|first=Leonidas|authorlink=|title=Forms of Hatred: The Troubled Imagination in Modern Philosophy and Literature|url=|year=2003|publisher=Rodopi|isbn=9042010665}} * {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Draper|first=Hal|authorlink=Hal Draper|title=Karl Marx’s Theory of Revolution|url=|year=1989|publisher=NYU Press|isbn=0853457972}} * {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Klier|first=John Doyle|authorlink=|title=Imperial Russia's Jewish Question, 1855-1881|url=|year=2005|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=0521023815}} * {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Livak|first=Leonid|authorlink=|title=The Jewish Persona in the European Imagination: A Case of Russian Literature|url=|year=2010|publisher=Stanford University Press|isbn=0804775621}} * {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Webman|first=Esther|authorlink=|title=The Global Impact of the Protocols of the Elders of Zion: A Century-Old Myth |url=|year=2011|publisher=Routledge|isbn=0415598923}} {{refend|2}}
